that Evagrius’ apophatic,
contemplative approach to theology/doctrine facilitates his teaching of apatheia
 – 
 the practice of negating multiple desires to mystically experience divine union. Essentially in doing so, Evagrius unites mysticism and asceticism, theological construction and spiritual experience. His apophatic asceticism is a fully integrated theology consisting of spiritualized thought and action.},
